    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2584: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Commissioner in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-07T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Your September 2, 9 A.M.</p>
                <p>The Department perceives no objection to proposed changes 2 and 3 except that
                    portion of change 3 after sub-quotation should read <pb facs="0165" n="51"
                        xml:id="pg_51"/> “the two Governments concerned agree in interpreting this
                    stipulation in the sense that in accordance with article 3 of the convention of
                    1907 et cetera With regard to proposed change 1, however, the Department would
                    feel it necessary to insist upon the following reservation, to be added as final
                    phrase of article: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Subject, however, to the right of diplomatic intervention in appropriate
                            cases and in accordance with the generally accepted rules and principles
                            of international law”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
